#: ../../pilot/moonbit-pilot/commands.md:1
msgid "Commands"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pilot/moonbit-pilot/commands.md:3
msgid "Markdown Files as Executables"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pilot/moonbit-pilot/commands.md:5
msgid ""
"Markdown files are executable, and the runtime environment is MoonBit "
"Pilot!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pilot/moonbit-pilot/commands.md:7
msgid "Background"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pilot/moonbit-pilot/commands.md:9
msgid "If you frequently have repetitive commands to execute, such as:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pilot/moonbit-pilot/commands.md:12
msgid "Run `pnpm lint --fix` until all errors are fixed\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pilot/moonbit-pilot/commands.md:16
msgid ""
"Copy-pasting this phrase every time becomes tedious, especially when you "
"have many prompts to execute. MoonBit Pilot provides a solution to make "
"managing your daily work prompts simple."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pilot/moonbit-pilot/commands.md:18
msgid "Final Effect"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pilot/moonbit-pilot/commands.md:20
msgid "Let's look at the final way to run the prompt:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pilot/moonbit-pilot/commands.md:22
msgid "/lint_fix\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pilot/moonbit-pilot/commands.md:26
msgid ""
"Here, you only need to run a `/lint_fix` command to complete the "
"execution of the above prompt."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pilot/moonbit-pilot/commands.md:28
msgid "Implementation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pilot/moonbit-pilot/commands.md:30
msgid ""
"In your project's `.moonagent/commands` directory, create a `lint_fix.md`"
" file with the following content:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pilot/moonbit-pilot/commands.md:32
msgid "Run pnpm lint --fix until all errors are fixed\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pilot/moonbit-pilot/commands.md:36
msgid ""
"Then you can use `lint_fix` as a command in the moon pilot command line, "
"with auto-completion support."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pilot/moonbit-pilot/commands.md:38
msgid "Handling Dynamic Prompts"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pilot/moonbit-pilot/commands.md:40
msgid ""
"What if you want the command to be changeable? You can modify the file "
"content like this:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pilot/moonbit-pilot/commands.md:42
msgid "Run {{args[0] or \"pnpm lint --fix\"}} until all errors are fixed\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pilot/moonbit-pilot/commands.md:46
msgid "Explanation:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pilot/moonbit-pilot/commands.md:48
msgid ""
"`args` represents positional arguments, which can be referenced using "
"`[index]`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pilot/moonbit-pilot/commands.md:49
msgid ""
"`kwargs` represents key-value pair arguments, which can be referenced "
"using `kwargs.<key>`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pilot/moonbit-pilot/commands.md:50
msgid "`{{}}` is used to render a value"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pilot/moonbit-pilot/commands.md:52
msgid "Let's see how to use it:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pilot/moonbit-pilot/commands.md:54
msgid "act ▶ /lint_fix \"echo hello\"\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pilot/moonbit-pilot/commands.md:58
msgid "You can also use named parameters:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pilot/moonbit-pilot/commands.md:60
msgid "Run {{kwargs.command or \"pnpm lint --fix\"}} until all errors are fixed\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pilot/moonbit-pilot/commands.md:64
msgid "Then use it like this:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pilot/moonbit-pilot/commands.md:66
msgid "act ▶ /lint_fix command=\"echo hello\"\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pilot/moonbit-pilot/commands.md:70
msgid "Notice that the value should be quote with `\"`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pilot/moonbit-pilot/commands.md:72
msgid "Complex Scripts"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pilot/moonbit-pilot/commands.md:74
msgid ""
"Here's an example of a more complex script to help you quickly complete "
"complex engineering requirements:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pilot/moonbit-pilot/commands.md:76
#, python-format
msgid ""
"# {{ kwargs.title or \"Development Plan\" }}\n"
"\n"
"## Objective\n"
"{{ kwargs.objective or \"Define the main objective here\" }}\n"
"\n"
"## Tasks\n"
"{% for task in args %}\n"
"- {{ task }}\n"
"{% endfor %}\n"
"\n"
"## Parameters\n"
"{% for key, value in kwargs %}\n"
"- **{{ key }}**: {{ value }}\n"
"{% endfor %}\n"
"\n"
"## Summary\n"
"Total tasks: {{ args|length }}\n"
"Total parameters: {{ kwargs|length }}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pilot/moonbit-pilot/commands.md:97
msgid ""
"Of course, for convenience, it's reasonable to minimize the number of "
"parameters."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pilot/moonbit-pilot/commands.md:99
msgid "Additional Benefits"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pilot/moonbit-pilot/commands.md:101
msgid ""
"Besides completing prompt management and improving execution efficiency, "
"this actually means you can better use IDE editors to write complex "
"prompts and make debugging easier."
msgstr ""

